Ltd. (CETV)  gained, reversing earlier losses, after the broadcaster
said today it agreed to repurchase its 2014 bonds for $71.1
million as part of a plan to lower the companyâ€™s indebtedness.  CME, as the company is known, jumped as much as 11 percent,
the most in two months, and traded up 2.2 percent to 110.26
koruna by 3:19 p.m. in Prague. The stock earlier slumped as much
